

<p><H2>README</H2></p>
<p><H3>Adding and Remove an Economic Event</H3></p>
<p>Please follow these steps to add a scheduled economic event:</p>
<ul>
    <li><b>Symbol:</b> Symbol should be the currency symbol that the event has an impact on.</li>
    <li><b>Announcement DateTime:</b> The release date of the event.</li>
    <li><b>Annoucement Name:</b> The name of the event. This is important please copy and paste to avoid typo.</li>
</ul>

<p>Once completed, click <b>Save</b> and wait until a message shows up next to the <b>Save</b> button with ID of the economic event. The added economic event would be displayed at the table below. The <b>Binary's Category</b> column shows the impact and duration of impact of the event on the currency pairs.</p>

<p>If you wish to delete an economic event, click on the <b>Delete</b> button. The event will be removed from the table and it will be listed under the <b>Deleted Economic Events</b> table. To restore the deleted event, Click on the <b>Restore</b> button.</p>

<p><H3>Economic Event Factors</H3></p>
<p></p>
<ul>
    <li><b>vol_change:</b> This is represent the estimated volatiltiy change after and before economic event release for the duration of effect. This value will be provided from economic_events_volatilities.yml by default.</li>
    <li><b>duration:</b> This is the duration after release which the volatility change decay to zero. This value is 20 minutes unless manually we change it.</li>
    <li><b>decay_factor:</b> decay_factor represents how fast the decay function decays. Mathematically more than 2/3 of varience belongs to duration/decay_factor. This value will be provided from economic_events_volatilities.yml by default.</li>
    <li><b>vol_change_before:</b> Sometimes market is volatile before the economic event release. This is the estimation of volatality change before release correlated with it. This value will be provided from economic_events_volatilities.yml by default.</li>
    <li><b>duration_before:</b>This is the duration before release which the volatility start rise from to zero. This value is 10 minutes unless manually we change it.</li>
    <li><b>decay_factor_before:</b> It is exactly same concept for before news impact. The values are provided on yaml file.</li>
<ol>
    <li>Default: This will keep existing decay factor value. For freshly added underlying to news it will be 20 for after and 10 for before.
    <li>Fast: Most of variance belongs to 1 minute after or before news. 
    <li>Slow: Most of variance belongs to half of time of duration after or before news.</li>
    <li>Flat: Variance is distributed evently all over the duration.</li>
</ol>
</ul>
<p><H3>Add Economic Event Factors</H3></p>
<p></p>
<p>If you wish to update the economic event factor for an economic event, input all factors and use <b>Update</b> to add for each underlying. Wait until a message shows up next to the button with 'ok'. There is option also to add the value to all direct or indirect pairs.</p>

